      "writtenOn": "2018-12-27T23:38:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This seems to add unnecessary complication, requiring the pipe to maintain a state machine to receive input.  With AsyncMessagePipe, you\u0027ll always receive complete packets, so you don\u0027t need to split it apart.\n\nPersonally, I would first confirm that the message is at least 4 bytes, then call onCommand with the additional data:\n\nuint32_t command \u003d *(uint32_t*)input.data();\nonCommand(command, input.size() - 4, input.data() + 4);\n\nThen, in onCommand I would do a switch on the command type, confirm the expected data length, and then dispatch to helper functions to handle, such as:\n\nuint32_t address \u003d *(uint64_t*)(additionalData);\nuint32_t size \u003d *(uint64_t*)(additionalData + 8);\nonRegionCommand(command, address, size);",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 217,
        "startChar": 16,
        "endLine": 219,
        "endChar": 59
